		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent">They let you power off at any time, and resume the game with no problem.</div>
<br />
<br />Interesting. I take it they keep two internal saves that are refreshed often, with a single byte selecting which one is the most recent. This way even if you power off in the middle of saving to one of the internal states, the other completely consistent one will be selected by this byte.

		

		</td>
