	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I think so, while I've no clue how the game works internally. The manual doesn't recommand to do this though, it says to use the "suspend" comand, and precise that if the power goes off anytime the previous sate is normally "suspended", so the manual doesn't say the poweroff automatic "suspend" is reliable.
<br />Also I think the game has its state saved each time the player have to interact, and each time an unit (player or enemy) has chosen its command, to prevent the player cheating with this if he make a big mistake. This couldn't be done if the save mode would be flash ROM, EEPROM or whathever, with very slow write times.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


